description: Close plan -> status/diff -> commit+push (with confirmation)
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git Plan Workflow: close

When the user indicates the plan is finished/completed/done:

1. Ensure all checklist items in the plan markdown are completed before closing:
   - In the repository plan file under `docs/plans/`, convert every pending checkbox from `- [ ]` to `- [x]` for completed work.
   - If any tasks are not actually done, stop and ask the user before marking them complete.
2. Ensure the repository plan markdown under `docs/plans/` is prefixed with `[completed]`:
   - If not prefixed yet, ask for confirmation before renaming to `[completed] <original>.md` within `docs/plans/`.
3. Review changes:
   - `git status`
   - `git diff` (and staged diff if needed)
4. Propose a concise commit message consistent with repository style.
5. Ask explicit confirmation before executing side-effect commands:
   - `git add ...`
   - `git commit`
   - `git push` or `git push -u origin HEAD` (only if upstream is missing)
6. After the commands succeed, report:
   - branch name used
   - commit hash
   - push destination (remote + branch)

Never auto-commit/auto-push without user confirmation.
